WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.720 --> 00:00:06.940
Have a challenging childhood with unreliable, reckless, or scary parents.

00:00:06.940 --> 00:00:11.700
Then, try never to think about, understand, or digest what you've been through.

00:00:11.700 --> 00:00:16.180
Grow up into an extremely romantic person with a firm conviction that there is

00:00:16.180 --> 00:00:21.640
someone out there who will entirely understand and heal the broken parts of you.

00:00:21.640 --> 00:00:26.040
Foster a faith in "the one": an angel in human form.

00:00:26.279 --> 00:00:32.439
Dismiss a lot of candidates with healthy
emotional backgrounds by saying that they are boring.

00:00:32.440 --> 00:00:35.820
Head for someone with similarly grave psychological wounds

00:00:35.820 --> 00:00:41.480
but far more importantly with an equal
commitment to not understanding themselves.

00:00:41.480 --> 00:00:43.860
Spent a lot of money on a huge wedding.

00:00:43.860 --> 00:00:46.739
Think at length about seating plans and flowers.

00:00:46.739 --> 00:00:49.639
Don't go anywhere near a marriage
therapist.

00:00:49.640 --> 00:00:52.820
Acquire some distinctive communication skills

00:00:52.820 --> 00:00:58.780
where when you are annoyed you don't really let on maybe drink or chop wood instead.

00:00:58.780 --> 00:01:03.140
Ask yourself if it's normal to be a bit unhappy with someone sometimes.

00:01:03.140 --> 00:01:05.980
An answer with a firm, "No."

00:01:05.980 --> 00:01:09.980
Trust that life for others is a bed of roses.

00:01:09.990 --> 00:01:13.070
Feel very justified in your own positions.

00:01:13.070 --> 00:01:15.060
Nurture self-righteousness.

00:01:15.060 --> 00:01:16.940
Stick to your guns.

00:01:16.940 --> 00:01:21.320
Be very insistent and keen on identifying your partner's wrongdoings.

00:01:21.320 --> 00:01:24.500
Become a forensic expert in their flaws.

00:01:24.500 --> 00:01:28.440
Adopt a general line that it's always the other person's fault.

00:01:28.440 --> 00:01:33.720
Be very good at explaining why criticism of you is misguided and cruel.

00:01:33.720 --> 00:01:37.660
Always believe that any feedback about you is malevolent.

00:01:37.660 --> 00:01:42.980
Insist that love is about accepting the whole of you, every single bit.

00:01:42.980 --> 00:01:47.840
Always measure your current sentiment against the happiest day of your honeymoon.

00:01:47.840 --> 00:01:51.460
And be very good at noting how far it's fallen.

00:01:52.290 --> 00:01:58.860
Carefully compare your daily experience
with the media representations of newly engaged celebrities.

00:01:58.860 --> 00:02:03.740
Draw frequent attention to the aging process as it affects your partner.

00:02:03.740 --> 00:02:07.160
Blame them for not taking care of themselves enough.

00:02:07.160 --> 00:02:11.740
Frequently identify people in the street with whom you might be much happier.

00:02:12.040 --> 00:02:14.400
Point them out to your partner.

00:02:14.690 --> 00:02:18.810
Watch a lot of porn and judge your own
sexual life by comparison

00:02:19.280 --> 00:02:23.020
Notice how many disappointing
characteristics in your own children are

00:02:23.030 --> 00:02:26.030
the fault of your partner and your
partner's family.

00:02:27.180 --> 00:02:31.560
Draw enormous inferences from your partner's irritating quirks of behavior

00:02:31.560 --> 00:02:33.960
around the kitchen and bathroom.

00:02:33.960 --> 00:02:39.080
Often ruminate on what potential damage your partner could have done to your career.

00:02:39.480 --> 00:02:44.860
Take your anger and disappointment with
your partner and direct it towards having an affair.

00:02:45.680 --> 00:02:50.980
Argue that divorce is just an accident,
means nothing, and the children won't mind.

00:02:51.040 --> 00:02:53.440
Get a divorce. Remarry.

00:02:53.450 --> 00:02:56.230
Add tears. Start again.

